    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"ddb\">\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">You point at a location within range, and a glowing, 1-foot-diameter ball of emerald &amp;Reference[acid]{acid} streaks there and explodes in a 20-foot-radius &amp;Reference[sphere]{sphere}. Each creature in that area must make a &amp;Reference[dex]{Dexterity} saving throw. On a failed save, a creature takes 10d4 &amp;Reference[acid]{acid} damage and another 5d4 &amp;Reference[acid]{acid} damage at the end of its next turn. On a successful save, a creature takes half the initial damage and no damage at the end of its next turn.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\"><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Inline-Subhead-Serif\"><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong>Â </span>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 5th level or higher, the initial damage increases by 2d4 for each slot level above 4th.</p>\n</div>",
